President Obama will deliver a speech on Monday, March 28 at 7:30PM ET at the National Defense University in Washington, DC. The purpose of the speech is to update the American people on the situation in Libya, including the actions taken with allies and partners to protect the Libyan people from Moammar Qaddafi's brutality, the transition to NATO command and control, and the policy going forward. The speech will be pooled for TV and open to correspondents. More details, including press credentialing information, will be released soon.